		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We present and compare learning rate schedules for stochastic gradient descent, a general algorithm which includes LMS, on-line backpropaga-tion and k-means clustering as special cases. We introduce &quot;search-then-converge&quot; type schedules which outperform the classical constant and &quot;running average&quot; (1ft) schedules both in speed of convergence and quality of solution.</p>
